12/01/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul praised the new Iraq strategy announced by US President George Bush and stressed that Ankara will continue constructive dialogue and co-operation with Washington to ensure the stability and unity of neighbouring Iraq.
Gul made the statement at a joint press conference Thursday (January 11th) with visiting Egyptian counterpart Ahmed Abul Gheit.
For his part, Abul Gheit said violence and clashes in Iraq must be curbed, adding that all militant groups must be eliminated so that the Iraqi administration can function.
He added that Egypt stands ready to provide full support, including training the Iraqi army.
(The New Anatolian, Zaman - 12/01/07;
AFP, AP, Xinhua - 11/01/07)
